ocp4-cis-node-master-file-permissions-cni-conf	"As a user with administrator privileges, log into a node in the relevant pool:

$ oc debug node/$NODE_NAME

At the sh-4.4# prompt, run:

# chroot /host


Then,run the command:
$ ls -l /etc/cni/net.d/*
If properly configured, the output should indicate the following permissions:
-rw-------"	"sh-4.4# chroot /host
sh-5.1# ls -l /etc/cni/net.d/*
-rw-r--r--. 1 root root 469 Apr 10 18:29 /etc/cni/net.d/100-crio-bridge.conflist
-rw-r--r--. 1 root root 129 Apr 10 18:29 /etc/cni/net.d/200-loopback.conflist
sh-5.1#"	
